sentence: U.S. stock futures were higher on Tuesday after European Central Bank board member Benoit Caeure said the bank will "frontload" its asset purchasing program in May and June to maintain a monthly average of 60 billion euros ($67 billion) as buying slows down during the summer.
Caeure was speaking at a conference in London.
In economic data out today, housing starts in April, out at 8:30 a.m.
E.T., are expected to have edged higher to 1.029 million from 926,000 in March, in the consensus range between 970,000 to 1.120 million.
Housing permits are expected to be up at 1.070 million compared to 1.039 million in March, in the consensus range between 1.050 million and 1.120 million.
In equities, Wal-Mart Stores ( WMT ) was down over 2% in recent pre-market trade as its fiscal Q1 earnings and revenue missed analysts' estimates.
Meanwhile, home improvement retailer Home Depot ( HD ) rose over 1% after its Q1 beat estimates, with comparable sales up 6.1% in the quarter.
